HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 347
BY REPRESENTATIVE BRAUD
HIGHWAYS: Urges and requests the Department of Transportation and Development to
study modifying toll operations within the state
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Department of Transportation and Development to study the
3 feasibility of establishing uniform toll signage, toll dispute procedures, and toll
4 customer service centers at all toll facilities within a certain radius.
5 WHEREAS, there are three bridges with tolls in Louisiana, namely: the Belle Chasse
6 Bridge, the Louisiana 1 Highway Bridge, and the Lake Pontchartrain Causeway Bridge; and
7 WHEREAS, the state of Louisiana is under contract with the Plenary Group for the
8 construction and management of the Belle Chasse Bridge, utilizing tolls to assist in financing
9 the project; and
10 WHEREAS, multiple lawsuits, including but not limited to contractual and
11 constitutional claims, involving the parish of Plaquemines government, residents of
12 Plaquemines, the Department of Transportation and Development, and the Plenary Group
13 involve a multitude of issues with toll collections and operations; and
14 WHEREAS, residents were charged expensive and inconsistent administrative fees,
15 not advertised throughout the bridge's development, with no explanation for the varying
16 costs; and
17 WHEREAS, residents were not being given a fair chance to challenge these fees with
18 any sort of appeal process; and
19 WHEREAS, one resident and plaintiff in the suit stated that he had to pay $1,600 in
20 administrative fees and at one point, his account was billed a $25 administrative fee eighteen
21 times in one day; and
