1 WHEREAS, in the period of tolling from May 2025 to October 2, 2025, $6,779,337
2 in fees and penalties were charged compared to $5,178,012.67 billed in actual toll charges;
3 and
4 WHEREAS, there are no toll fee signs to indicate actual toll rates and the cost of tolls
5 for those crossing the Belle Chasse Bridge; and
6 WHEREAS, there is only one customer service center in Golden Meadow for the
7 Belle Chasse toll bridge, which is over ninety miles away and a four hour round trip; and
8 WHEREAS, toll fees are impeding the ability of local businesses to earn a living; and
9 WHEREAS, toll and administrative fees are excessive and lack uniformity; and
10 WHEREAS, multiple small businesses, including but not limited to Salvo's Seafood,
11 have provided testimony at multiple Joint Transportation, Highways and Public Works
12 hearings; and
13 WHEREAS, testimony has included numerical and graphical proof that the toll rates,
14 fees, and penalties caused a significant decline in their sales; and
15 WHEREAS, the appeals process for challenging toll fees is inconsistent and difficult
16 for residents to navigate; and
17 WHEREAS, the lack of uniform toll signage, toll dispute procedures, and toll
18 customer service centers within a certain radius have all served to complicate the lives of
19 residents, business owners, and customers alike.
20 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
21 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request that the Department of Transportation
22 and Development study the feasibility of establishing uniform toll signage, toll dispute
23 procedures, and toll customer service centers at all toll facilities within a certain radius.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Transportation and
25 Development shall submit a written report to the House Committee on Transportation,
26 Highways and Public Works, by February 1, 2027, detailing its findings on ways to establish
27 uniform toll signage, the most efficient procedures for toll disputes, and the benefits of
28 establishing toll customer service centers at all toll facilities within a close radius of the toll
29 bridge.
